TITLE: Georgia high court reinstates ban on abortions after 6 weeks
SUMMARY: Abortion providers who had resumed performing the procedure will again have to stop

TITLE: Sen. Lisa Murkowski wins re-election in Alaska, fending off Trump-backed challenger Kelly Tshibaka
SUMMARY: Murkowski, one of only seven Republicans who voted to convict Trump at his second impeachment trial, emerged victorious after the race went to a ranked-choice runoff

TITLE: Black voters in Louisiana ‘embarrassed’ by state’s failure to pass anti-slavery amendment
SUMMARY: “Are they trying to trick us into voting for slavery?” asked John Miles, a 41-year-old Black truck driver in Monroe

TITLE: Former Rep. David Rivera of Florida is arrested in Venezuela probe
SUMMARY: Rivera, a Republican who served from 2011 to 2013, was arrested at Atlanta’s airport, according to a spokesperson for the U.S. Attorney’s Office in Miami

TITLE: Jury deliberations begin in Trump Organization tax fraud trial
SUMMARY: The 12-person jury deliberated for more than four hours Monday before breaking for the day. They will resume on Tuesday morning

TITLE: U.S. says it will expand, extend temporary status for Haitians
SUMMARY: A cholera outbreak, malnutrition and attacks by increasingly bold gangs since the president's assassination in 2021 make forced return too dangerous, DHS says

TITLE: Top elections official in Texas resigns
SUMMARY: Secretary of State John Scott, who was appointed by Republican Gov. Greg Abbott, was briefly part of Trump’s legal team that challenged the results of the 2020 election

TITLE: Giuliani 'weaponized his law license' in 2020 election case, ethics counsel says
SUMMARY: A Washington, D.C., disciplinary panel heard charges that Giuliani violated attorney ethics rules in a failed election fraud lawsuit challenging former President Donald Trump's 2020 loss

TITLE: Police officers to receive Congressional Gold Medals for Jan. 6
SUMMARY: Hundreds of officers will be recognized with Congress’s highest honor nearly two years after they fought with former President Donald Trump’s supporters in a brutal and bloody attack

TITLE: More than 70% of voters in poll want Biden to release secret JFK assassination records
SUMMARY: The records, which could shed light on ties between Lee Harvey Oswald and the CIA, are supposed to be released Dec. 15. But they still could be delayed
